.cs 3 on
.item 'SET NOTIME Command' 'Added on 08/24/90 by JLS'
.boxon
SET NOTIME n
.boxoff

.* DESCRIPTION
The SET NOTIME command allows you to change the number of minutes of inactivity
after which you are warned and then logged off (if there is no response to the
warning).  The default timeout interval is 240 minutes (4 hours).

SHOW NOTIME displays your current timeout interval.

.* SELECT 'SET NOTIME Command Options'
.us Option Descriptions

.* OPTION N
.optix n
n\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\specifies the number of minutes of inactivity after which you
                wish to be warned and then logged off. The default is 240.
                SET NOTIME 0 gives you unlimited idle time.
.cs 3 off
